From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Makefile: disable stack protector for bare-metal build

Buildroot's internal RISC-V toolchain enables stack protector by default.
OpenSBI links without the userspace stack protector runtime, so the build
fails with undefined references to __stack_chk_guard/__stack_chk_fail.

Disable stack protector explicitly for the firmware build.
---
 Makefile | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
index dca7afd..ecb799b 100644
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -211,6 +211,7 @@ CFLAGS		+=	$(GENFLAGS)
 CFLAGS		+=	$(platform-cflags-y)
 CFLAGS		+=	$(firmware-cflags-y)
 CFLAGS		+=	-fno-pie -no-pie
+CFLAGS		+=	-fno-stack-protector
 
 CPPFLAGS	+=	$(GENFLAGS)
 CPPFLAGS	+=	$(platform-cppflags-y)
-- 
